And mostly they talked about his hobbies, and that he was in the hiking club, and he had been helping Cheri with some stuff around the house, so Cheri is Nick's wife.

Mostly talked about hobbies, he is in the hiking club, too, apparently, said he has been helping Cheri with some stuff around the house, just trying to be a friend in her time of need. On my way out, I took a peek into his car, noticed something that might be useful. Ran into him at the Limestone [00:39:00] Diner, gave me a bunch of platitudes about moving on with your life…oh, moving on with your life?

After he was done condescending to me, he went to pay his bill and left his pocket notebook sitting out on the table, I couldn't resist tearing out a page, too bad I didn't get more. Showed up at my house later that night, scared me half to death, banging on the door, accused me of theft, threatening to press charges. I know he won't, if he couldn't even figure out that Nick was murdered, there is no way he will be able to prove anything." Oh, my god, [00:40:00] too many… Okay.
